Transparency Moment:
I have been running from the calling on my life and this is the first time where I've felt exposed.

Growing up in the church, I vowed to never go back to it and live my life as I wanted to. Even rewatching the video and hearing me say "the world's way" rubbed me the wrong way because it makes it seems that anything outside of the church is wrong and everything in the church is right.

Having experienced church/religious trauma made me want to do any and everything that was considered "unholy" or "like the world." When the truth is, most of my actions made me feel empty. Yes, I could have sex, drink, party, and buy nice things to stunt on people. But what about the times I would go home feeling lost or unhappy with the desires of my heart given 10-fold? I would hear people speak on their relationship with God, and at one point, I couldn't get excited at all because the guilt of living my life any kind of way made me feel shame to even mention God. However, God was there all along and never left me. God wasn't ashamed of me either. God had been wanting a relationship with me and wanting to be the biggest part of my life, and I didn't. I wanted the success, the relationship, the money, and all things shiny without God. I can be honest about that. 

Before this time, the idea of having a relationship with God (in my mind) was transactional or a dictatorship. Nothing loving. Nothing faithful. Nothing kind. Nothing beautiful. You may be wondering how I got here: before New Year's Eve, I asked God to help me build a relationship between us. Every thing that I idolized got snatched from me in days. 

Reflecting now, I can have the most fulfilling life, businesses, and everything fabulous but I need that spirit to spirit connection with the Most High. 

Not going to lie, it stung at first. Now, I'm slowly understanding what needed to go in order for me and God to be closer and for me to have this relationship. It's no longer about being religious, but more so having a relationship. It's changing me daily and it's hard. However, maybe this testimony can help someone who grew up in the church like me and go tired of playing church.

Y'all can't know how healing this video was to make.

I grew up a kid with curves. I got reminded at home, at school, at church, and damn there everywhere that I was my skinny like the other girls. I should have had a better support system back then, but I've decided to build my own support system now. I'm finally back in the gym, trusting myself and my decisions, learning to pick better foods, and loving the body that I am in the way it is now. I decided that I wouldn't wait until my body for 20 pounds lighter, 40 pounds lighter, or even 80 pounds lighter. I've decided to love myself with every step and with every pound lost.

This is my declaration to myself: love me and love God. Learning how to fully love God and to fully love me. Not love me because of my skin tone; not love me because people celebrate me; not love me because a man told me that I was fine. No! Love me for me with all of my attributes, flaws, fat, and every thing in between! 

I just want to make little De'Shundra proud! She deserves this win, too! Also, I'm doing this journey wearing the apparel I want to wear, while visioning the way I want my body to look.

I just knew as a kid that I would have become a famous writer or attorney. I attended Jackson State University (S/O to #TheeILove) and obtained 2 degrees in Political Science. On my way to Washington! 

I became a wardrobe stylist. A full account, @stylebydnicole! 

I could have sworn as a kid, I would be married by now with at least 3 little girls! I'm currently single without kids living in Atlanta.

I didn't turn out the way I thought I would. HOWEVER, I'm very happy with myself (even while I discover me and heal). I'm not ashamed of my journey. No baby! Not at all! I look in the mirror and I'm proud of me. Something that I couldn't say 10 years ago at 24 confused, hurting, and masking everything deep within!

I didn't end up the power multi-million dollar lawyer. I did, however, become a powerful (soon to be) millionaire wardrobe stylist who loves herself, loves God, and finding her place in the world DAILY!
Yesterday was a GREAT day and I needed to smile! I pin curled my wig, too! ♥️

I refuse to be that "big girl" that chooses to not embrace the body that has kept me safe for so long!

I've been on my weight loss journey for a few weeks now. It hasn't been hard; more like adjusting. I've been adjusting my meals, have cut out my favorite diet soda, and going to the gym weekly.

I've made a decision to slay every step of this journey. I won't be deleting my "fat" photos. I won't be verbally trashing my current body. I won't be calling myself ugly names. I won't be dissing and dismissing me at my highest weight, while popping my shit when I get to my smallest. NOPE! I'm gone pop my shit EVERY CHANCE I GET.

I know my life will change once I'm "small." I know roses will be thrown at my feet. The NBA & NFL players will be back (as they were in my early 20s). The attention will be extreme. None of that shit will mean nothing to me. I've been healing my relationship with food and exercise. I don't see the gym as a chore. I don't see healthy eating as a battle. Y'all, each day, I'm closer to my ideal mindset that will open doors to my ideal lifestyle that will open doors to my ideal body and beauty standard. It's all about me. ME! This time, it's about ME and me finally prioritizing my health and wellness.

One thing about it, I'm going to show up to the gym in my usual fashion: SLAYAGE!

Now, I actually workout in my @sbdncapparel hoodie but these sets are from @rebdolls! I be sexy and sweaty underneath that hoodie, too!

SN: one thing about it, I'm going to be me. My body is changing and I'm happy to continue the journey. I refuse to be ashamed for how it looks. I'm going to love on me and show up as my most fabulous self, living in complete color.

How often do you talk to your inner child? Me? I talk to mine WEEKLY (sometimes daily).

I check in with her and let her know that I love her, respect her, promise to protect her, and forever be her biggest fan. 

In the past, I used to be mean to her. Very mean! I took on those projections I developed from bullying, not feeling pretty, and not being my own best friend out of her. It hurt realizing how much I would use my own mental and emotional state as a punching bag. Not cool at all! 

With my therapist & journaling, I find myself loving on myself more every day. I still overthink. I still am my biggest critic. I put A LOT of pressure on myself. However, I'm learning how to give myself grace. 

I'm constantly living in color the way little De'Shundra would want me to!

Transparency Time:

What was supposed to be a YouTube/Influencer room has become an actual quiet time/sanctuary for me.

I've been struggling this year BIG TIME with my walk with Christ. Parts of me are with it, while parts of me are struggling to fully believe or want to participate. I'm nothing like the believers with amazing faith and incredible relationships. Nah! I'm one that finds it's difficult to pray, difficult to believe, and difficult to understand why me.

One of the matters that I have to work on the most is my love walk. Honey! I can be a woman that will ignore you, hold a grudge, and find myself not caring too much. On the flip side, if I know I'm not in the right mind or spirit, I'll keep away from people and stay to myself. This spiritual warfare is something else.

Throughout it all, I'm seeking the truth spiritually in this room because I desire to change; I desire to be in communion with my faith, my ancestors, and my spirit guides who are looking out for me. I desire a relationship with God and know Spirit's son and identifying Spirit without ever losing faith. It's TOUGH! However, I won't fold!

Yesterday, I had a talk with my aunt @mel_writerlife and she encouraged me to be as vulnerable and transparent for the sake of not only healing but being a light. 

I've been on a lifestyle/weight loss journey since February. I've had good weeks and not so good weeks. Recently, someone made a comment and it brought me to a place of being a kid again: feeling fat and unattractive. Unless you've been overweight in your life, you can't imagine what emotional and mental battles a person deals with being in a body that feels like its trapped. The comment offended TF out of me and it made me want to starve myself for the week and just break down emotionally. However, I decided not to go with my emotions. What good would that do, right? None! I've pulled myself out of that mental sadness and decided to eat better anyway. Go to the gym anyway. 

I'm learning my body. I'm learning my triggers. I'm recognizing that I emotionally eat. I recognize that it's unhealthy to look at food as a fix. I'm realizing that going to the gym isn't a chore and that I can go and have fun, get inspired by other people in the gym, and go at my own pace.

As of this moment, @sweetesttaboo_darlington & @msamberpriley are my fitness/body goals and I'm so happy to be on this journey. This is for me this time and I'm about to be fine AF!

Hey! I'm D. Ni'Cole! For the next 6 months, I'm on a ✨leveling up✨ journey that focuses on certain areas of my life that need improvement. Mentally, I need a completely mindset reset. Emotionally, learning to let go and release any anger, resentment, fear, hate, and past heartbreak. Spiritually, learning that God and I are 1. We cannot do this journey without each other and it's best for me to have a love rooted relationship with God instead of a transactional/religious one. Financially, learning to stop eating my seed and shopping my seed away. If I don't need it, don't buy it. Physically, continuing my diet/lifestyle change and being friends with the gym. 

Learning how to forgive with boundaries and having an in-depth love walk is going to be the biggest take away these next 6 months, and a self esteem boost. I'm recording every aspect of this journey because I know someone needs to see it and know that it's possible. 

Day 8 of 180. Let's goooooooo!

Thinking about starting my YT channel and uploading these transparency videos NOW! 

I'm officially in my 6 months of the ✨Leveling Up✨ journey and I received a surprised revelation: I cannot handle being loved. OUCH!!! The truth stung, but instead of getting offended, I decided to dig deep and figure out where this resistance to love came from. 

No matter what, you cannot our love, overly pour into, and see what you want to see when you're dealing with damaged people. You'll eventually become the damaged person. Toughening up myself to avoid being being hurt BACKFIRED. Had I known better, I would have never stopped walking in love but being choosey of who got that tender, intimate type of love from me. Essentially, everyone can experience certain parts of you (that's ok). Make everything known and be open to walk away when you're not receiving what you want!
That's it baby!

This weight loss journey is mine. It's going to be whatever it's going to be for me.

April wasn't the best month for me regarding consistency with the gym and eating healthy. This month, I've been triggered relentlessly through emotional turmoil. I walked away from a friendship that didn't end on the best note (actually it should have ended last May). I hit different financial challenges throughout the month and had to build a pivoting strategy for the rest of the second quarter. I fell back into some bad eating habits (small ones) and haven't been consistent with my protein intake. I noticed that when life starts lifing, I begin to emotionally eat. That's not good AT ALL. However, I'm showing myself grace and will be returning back to my gym/diet modifications. 

Even with my disappointments, I spotted sunshine. This dress was purchased last May. I wore it for the first time in August 2022. I JUST got into my weight loss journey in February. I tried this dress on for a date and I noticed the difference immediately. I haven't lost a significant amount of weight, but it feels good to see some progress.

My goal is to be down 81 pounds by December, while learning how to eat better and develop a fresh lifestyle for myself!

As anxiety fills my body, I have to understand what the Most High & the universe have been warning me about for some time now. 

Imagine saying, "Oh yes! I deserve a good life and good things to happen to me," while subconsciously believing the opposite. Insane, right? However, that's been my reality and I'm just now coming into grips of it. 

Recently, God/Spirit spoke to me and said, "You've been operating out of the energy/spirit of lack." I was SHOCKED! However, I noticed how my body would tense up at the idea of me receiving unexpected money that I had not worked hard for, love that I had not performed or worked hard for, praise that I felt like I didn't deserve, opportunities of business or personal advancement that I didn't feel worthy of receiving, and holding unto people and memories that no longer belonged in my life. I don't care what anyone says: where you're currently at in life, your self esteem, mindset, and habits are tied to it.

Doing the most shadow work that I've ever done in my life, I've noticed how many of the decisions that I make (and don't make) are influenced by how I see myself through the lenses of my physical attractiveness, confidence, and self esteem.

I want MORE. Taking time off from dating and being on the constant search for love or "the one," I've decided that for now I'm the love that I've been searching for. Pouring into myself and showing up for myself is new to me. When I'm chasing a dollar, it's easy for me to be punctual and follow through. When it comes to myself, I can be the most inconsistent person. Not to mention, I'm just as inconsistent if not more inconsistent with God. Something about that just isn't right. 

Let's see what it looks like when I choose to pour into myself (FIRST) and show up for myself for the next 365 days.

At the point, it's the best feeling.
I take it day at a time. Learning how to eat. Learning how far my body can go.

My aunt, @mel_writerlife is one of my BIGGEST supporters. Back in 2017, I was so frustrated with my life. June of that year, my aunt told me to get in a better social circle, separate myself from the noise, and FOCUS. At the time, I had no clue what the future would have brought. In November of that same year, my aunt asked me to create a business plan and she gifted me the start up cost to establish @sbdncapparel. 

6 years in business. I want to make it to see year 7. As a parent watching her child grow, I've watched my brand GROW and become who she is. I've watch the money made from my brand hire models, influencers, a part time assistant, brand manager, and lawyers. I've watched my brand seek and establish 5 USPTO registered trademarks. I've watched my brand show up on television and movies! 

The moment my brand found herself in a rough patch, I watched me turn my back on her. How typical of me! Every thing is good when the money is being made. What about the times the money isn't being made? Do I selfishly throw away the legacy that's now in my family? Or, do I nurture the brand and find new ways to love her, market her, continue to operate her in excellence, and speak life into her? 

I haven't had the pleasure of getting many things right. However, I was right about my brand. My aunt was right about my brand. GOD was right about my brand. 

I'm so grateful and thankful for the vision that was given to me to start and continue to operate @sbdncapparel! Even more, I thank @pmcmarketing, @stylemestephar, @clair_daily, @josephineleimamo, and @aishaavisuals for always being where I needed y'all to be!

The weight lifted off of my completely because it's not meant to be, why even entertain the thought? EXACTLY!

This is from 2 weeks ago.

I am a PERFECTIONIST and have been my biggest critic for YEARS! I'm very sure I picked that up from church and felt like I was never "good enough" (by whose standard I'm not sure). Being performative and highly critical (over the years) has poured into my friendships, situationships, potential relationships, and the relationship that I have with myself. How can one be at peace with oneself if there's always a battle within to be anything but authentic and true? 

This year has been like a mirror. When I'm mean to myself and speak down to myself, it's offending my inner child. Y'all, little De'Shundra is so fragile, sensitive, bubbly, and fun. Somehow, the world will tell you that being those things are bad. But what I am learning is speaking to myself as a flower and handling myself with grace and love is empowering!

I've grown significantly tired with beating myself up about things that are in my head or beyond my control. I don't have it all figured out. I'm not perfect. I'm not the things from my past. Quite frankly, I'm starting to become more and more focused on my happiness (only) and way of living, rather than if people can get jiggy with it! LOL!!

I know this seems like a rant but one thing I know my ranting does is LIBERATE people. Hell, I've been liberating myself and my understanding what it means to be me, loved, happy, successful, disciplined, enjoyed, and at peace with life. Getting out of cycles of terror and into cycles of freedom! The time is now.

From March 2023-today: I'm proud of myself. 

No! I didn't lose a significant amount of weight this year but I made sure to show up for myself like never before. In previous years, I would "promise" myself gym trips and better eating. I'm still learning.

To get me started, I purchased workout wear from @rebdolls, @oldnavy, and @savagexfenty to keep me motivated to go. I wore the same pieces and rotated them out over a 9 month period. I watched myself enjoy the gym more and more. I watched myself love me again. I watched my confidence rise. I watched me show up for me! 

I have another year of losing the weight I want to lose. I will successfully lose 80 pounds by next December. I cannot speak for anybody; I can only speak for me. In my eyes, I'm WINNING!!! I managed to face my childhood traumas regarding my weight, weight loss, exercise, healthy eating, and drinking water. It's only up!
